## Async and Await:
Async is a function who return a promise.
Await means wait, it just stop the execution of async after finishing one it go for 2nd then 3rd..
and Await only write on Async function not anywhere more..

For example:
This is my promise and the delay time ..

function task() {
  return new Promise((resolve) => {
    setTimeout(() => {
      resolve("Done");
    }, 2000);
  });
}

// This is how you will use the Async and await..

async function run() {                              //this is async function
  const result = await task();                        //it return the promise so you have to put it into a variable in here its result
  console.log(result);                                //function will print the result
}

run();                                          //finally you call the function.


//Parallekl example fast:
async function run() {
  const [a, b] = await Promise.all([task1(), task2()]);              //you just use the Promise.all and then what you want..
}


//Error handling:

async function run() {
  try {                                                            //use try for error
    const res = await task();
    console.log(res);
  } catch (err) {                                                          //use catch()
    console.log(err);
  }
}









